      	 	<div class="widget" id="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description__widget">
			<div class="notice_desc_dates">
				<span class="added">Added: <input type="hidden" name="dnf_class_values[procurement_notice][description][0][added_on]" value="2014-02-10 07:25:33">Feb 10, 2014 7:25 am</span>
					</div>
		<span><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">ACTION CODE: Presolicitation Notice/Procurement</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">DESCRIPTION: This acquisition includes the purchase of a code and part number item where PNEUDRAULICS, INC. (06177), AUSCO,INC. (06239), and HYDRAFLOW (24984) are the approved manufacturer(s) and/or has supplied the item in the past. The intent is to award an indefinite quantity type contract for a one year base and two option years. Solicitation and NSN will be available for download on the Internet at <a href="HTTPS://WWW.DIBBS.BSM.DLA.MIL"><span>HTTPS://WWW.DIBBS.BSM.DLA.MIL</span></a><span> on its issue date.</span></p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">PR NUMBER: 1000021829<br />SOLICITATION NUMBER: SPE7MC-14-X-0031<br />SOLICITATION DATE: 02/10/14<br />SOLICITATION IS AVAILABLE AT HTTPS://WWW.DIBBS.BSM.DLA.MIL<br /><br />THE PROPOSED CONTRACT IS 100% SET ASIDE FOR SMALL BUSINESS CONCERNS. THE SMALL BUSINESS SIZE STANDARD IS 500 EMPLOYEES.<br /><br />CLASSIFICATION CODE: 4820<br /><br />DATE SYNOPSIZED: 02/10/14<br /><br />CLOSING DATE: 02/24/14<br /><br />ANTICIPATED AWARD DATE: 03/07/14<br /><br />NSN AND NOMENCLATURE: 4820-01-044-0433 / VALUE, HYDRAULIC, REL</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">MANUFACTURER(s):</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">PNEUDRAULICS, INC. (06177) P/N: 1719-1A</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">AUSCO,INC. (06239) P/N: A359</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">HYDRAFLOW (24984) P/N: VA042</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left"><br /><br />QUANTITIES AND INCREMENTAL QUANTITIES</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">RANGE 1: 14 TO 29</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">RANGE 2: 30 TO 88</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">RANGE: 3 89 TO 147</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">RANGE 4: 148 TO 236</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">&nbsp;</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">DELIVERY SCHEDULED AS NEEDED. <br /><br />THE PROPOSED PROCURMENT CONTAINS AN OPTION TO EXTEND THE CONTRACT PERIOD ONE OR MORE TIMES AT THE DISCRETION OF THE GOVERNMEN. THE TOTAL DURATION (BASE PLUS OPTION YEARS) SHALL NOT EXCEED 3 YEARS OR $150,000.00 WHICHEVER COMES FIRST. <br /><br />IT IS ANTICIPATED THAT AWARD WILL BE MADE VIA A DELIVERY ORDER TO AN EXISTING BASED ORDERING AGREEMENT. <br /><br />WHILE PRICE MAY BE A SIGNIFICANT FACTOR IN THE EVALUATION OF OFFERS, THE FINAL AWARD DECISION WILL BE BASED UPON A COMBINATION OF PRICE, DELIVERY, PAST PERFORMANCE AND OTHER EVALUATION FACTURORS AS DESCRIBED IN THE SOLICITATION. <br /><br />DELIVERY: VARIES STOCK LOCATIONS</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">COUNTRY: UNITED STATES</p><br />
<p dir="ltr" align="left">** DLA INTERNET BID BOARD SYSTEM (DIBBS) QUOTATIONS ARE NOT ACCEPTABLE FOR THIS SOLICITATION. QUOETS MUST BE SUBMITTED ON A HARD COPY OF THIS REQUEST FOR QUOTE AND FAXED OR EMAILED TO LORI BENNETT AT 614-693-1605 OR</p><br />
</span><a href="mailto:LORI.BENNETT@DLA.MIL"><span>LORI.BENNETT@DLA.MIL</span></a><span>. PLEASE DIRECT QUESTIONS ABOUT THIS SOLICITATION TO THE SAME. **</span>


